<p>Mr. Khaleel Ibraheem Al Jaber, the president of Qatar Swimming Association (QSA) announced that QSA is planning to make “Mellouli Swimming Academy” as international swimming sport facility to contribute positively in turning Qatari swimmers into  international champions.</p><p>In press release to Qatar News Agency on Sunday, Mr. Al Jaber said:   it is great honor that the academy holds the name of Oussama Mellouli, Tunisian Olympic champion, who enjoys great support from fans and lovers here in State of Qatar.</p><p>“The QSA has great confidence that Melouli effort through the academy will educate, train and turn the children and young generation into world swimmers. As well as the Academy is open for all citizens and expatriates” said Al Jaber.</p>learn more <a href="http://www.olympic.qa/en/NewsCenter/Pages/Al-Jaber-unveils-Mellouli-Swimming-Academy-objectives.aspx">here</a>